This is a non-optimising compiler written in C++ I built before I came to university. 
Source files are written in a made up pseudocode and are translated to Python.
I wrote a BNF grammar detailing the language because I was interested. It can be found in grammar.txt

Build using "make all" and run using the following command

./bin/ppc data/hello.pcode

The generated file will be located in data/
Run it using "python3 data/hello.py"
